# Unity Feature Folder Layout

- New feature code should be grouped under `Assets/Game/Features/<FeatureName>/` when possible.
- The `Domain`, `Application`, `Presentation`, `Infrastructure`, and `Editor` split inside a feature should show layer responsibility.
- `Domain` and `Application` code must not reference Unity APIs; Unity-specific adapter/detail code belongs under `Presentation`, `Infrastructure`, or `Editor`.
- Tests should be grouped near production code or under an explicit test root with the same feature name.
- Vague folders such as `Utils`, `Helpers`, `Common`, and `Managers` should not be the default home for new behavior.
- Prefabs, scenes, `ScriptableObject`s, and UI assets should be separate from code but still tied to a feature/module authoring area.
- Move code to a shared area only when multiple features truly use it; do not globalize a single feature's needs.

## Example

```text
Assets/Game/Features/Economy/
  Domain/
  Application/
  Presentation/
  Tests/EditMode/
```
